Accessing Raspberry Pi remotely:

Step 1: Connecting Pi to Internet

	Method 1: Ethernet cable

	Method 2: Using monitor just once, connect to Wi-Fi

	Method 3: Connect laptop to Pi physically, use command line


Step 2: Pi is online

SSH (must be on same network):
    From Mac Terminal:
        ssh pawprint@raspberrypi.local
	Password: pawprint

	hostname -I (to find IP address)

VNC (Remote Desktop):
    From Real VNC Viewer:
        Enter the IP address found from SSH / Direct Connection
